last_episode_to_air.name: Ultimate Champion
last_episode_to_air.overview: It’s the last day of fishing and every boat is out trying to make one final paycheck and possibly secure the title - Champion of Champions.

name: Wicked Tuna: Outer Banks
overview: The long, cold winter has just hit New England, and while the bluefin tuna season has come to an end in Gloucester, Mass., it’s just getting started in the Outer Banks of North Carolina. After a disappointing season, several of Gloucester’s top fishermen head south to try to salvage their finances by fishing for the elusive bluefin tuna in unfamiliar Carolina waters before the experienced locals beat them to the catch. It’s a whole new battlefield and the Northern captains must conquer new styles of fishing, treacherous waters and the wrath of the Outer Banks’ top fishermen. They’re gambling on what could be a massive payday … or a huge financial loss.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: Several of Gloucester's top fishermen follow bluefin tuna south to the Outer Banks for winter.

episodes.name: Yankee Invasion
episodes.overview: After a disappointing North Atlantic bluefin tuna season, Captain Dave Marciano of the Hard Merchandise and Captain TJ Ott of the Hot Tuna travel south full steam into the waters of the Outer Banks, N.C., to extend their season and salvage their losses. In the South, the competition is fiercer and the stakes are higher than ever before. The 500-mile steam is a huge gamble on what could be a massive payday  or a huge financial loss.

episodes.name: Southern Discomfort
episodes.overview: The Southern captains fear a full-scale Yankee invasion of their waters when another Northern boat  the Pin Wheel with Captain Tyler McLaughlin  comes steaming into the Outer Banks. This trip, McLaughlin is desperate to make up for the embarrassing last-place finish he landed last season, and to help him he adds Paul Hebert onboard as co-captain. As the Pin Wheel steams in, they're greeted with gunshots by the Southerners, showing there is no room for Southern hospitality.

episodes.name: Bluefin or Bust
episodes.overview: With six of the finest tuna fisherman traversing the Outer Banks in the hunt for bluefin, competition gets super competitive. The strict bluefin quota is rapidly starting to fill, and time is of the essence for all the captains. Dave Marciano has been unable to land a single catch and fears the huge gamble he made in traveling south will not pay off. If he doesn't catch a fish in the next two days, he won't be able to afford to stay in the Carolinas and will have to head back to Gloucester.

episodes.name: We're Not in Gloucester Anymore
episodes.overview: Weather in the Outer Banks takes a turn for the worse, pitting man against sea as the turbulent Atlantic Ocean threatens the fishermen's quest for bluefin tuna. With ominous weather looming and the bluefin quota quickly filling, the pressure is on for the Northern and Southern boats to act fast or risk financial  or nautical  disaster. The Fishin' Frenzy leads the fleet and Captain Greg Mayer uses his knowledge of the Carolina waters to head out early before the windy weather escalates.

episodes.name: Ice Ice Tuna
episodes.overview: With more than a third of the North Carolina bluefin tuna quota already filled, all of the fleet feels the pressure to fish at every opportunity. So when an Atlantic Ocean winter storm system whips up rough seas and ices in the local harbor, it forces northern and southern captains to take huge risks to fish in dangerous conditions for their catch.

episodes.name: By Hook or By Crook
episodes.overview: A rivalry flares up between two top boats; a captain attempts to shake his losing streak; and a trip south must be paid for by hauling in more fish.

episodes.name: From Rods to Riches
episodes.overview: The Wahoo's lead is challenged as the Pin Wheel edges up the scoreboard. Elsewhere, mechanical troubles and bad fishing keep the rest of the ships from catching up.

episodes.name: Doghouse Afternoon
episodes.overview: The captain of the Doghouse charters boat cruises for supplemental income while the rest of the fleet continue to compete for leadership of the scoreboard.

episodes.name: Tick Tock Tuna
episodes.overview: Pin Wheel and rivals Fishin' Frenzy and Wahoo lead the race with seven tuna each. Captain Greg Mayer of Fishin' Frenzy is desperate for catches to reclaim their top spot, while the Wahoo brothers Reed and Banks Meredith are determined to stay in the top spot. Pin Wheel Co-Captains Tyler McLaughlin and Paul Hebert are a stone's throw away from beating all of the Southern boats in their own backyard. Doghouse, Hard Merchandise and Hot Tuna struggle to haul in fish for the remainder of the season.

episodes.name: The Fat Tuna Sings
episodes.overview: Wahoo leads the fleet, but local rival Fishin' Frenzy and invader Pin Wheel are serious threats for the top spot. Hard Merchandise needs one more bluefin to make the expensive trip south profitable, while Doghouse and Hot Tuna fight to earn one final paycheck to salvage their seasons. When captain Greg Mayer of Fishin' Frenzy receives the official call that the quota will close the next day at midnight, everyone races to catch more bluefin and reach the buyers in time to make the final sale.

episodes.name: First Strike
episodes.overview: It’s opening day of the Outer Banks bluefin season, and the captains battle it out to make the season’s first catch.

episodes.name: Bombs Away
episodes.overview: After colliding with Bonner Bridge, Captain Marciano and Captain Griffin struggle to regroup. The boats are banged up, but it’s too early to tell whether they can salvage their seasons or if they’ll have to hang up their rods.

episodes.name: Fins of the Father
episodes.overview: Charlie Griffin joins the crew of the Reels of Fortune before picking up his boat from the mechanics. Later, the northern captains play a prank on Tyler McLaughlin.

episodes.name: Salty Gals and Southern Nights
episodes.overview: Fishin' Frenzy have a slight lead over Reels of Fortune; Hot Tuna asks Reel Action for assistance; Doghouse is relying on their greenhorn to bring in the catch.

episodes.name: Wicked Ride
episodes.overview: At the start of the 11th day on the water in North Carolina, treacherous winter weather in the Outer Banks fishing grounds forces captains to push their limits. Southern boat Reels of Fortune holds a meager lead over last year’s local champion Fishin’ Frenzy, while northern boat Hard Merchandise and local all-female team Reel Action have yet to catch a fish.

episodes.name: Reels of Misfortune
episodes.overview: In North Carolina’s bluefin tuna fleet, family is at the forefront of the fight to fish hard and make money. On Fishin’ Frenzy, First Mate Nick Gowitzka faces a family emergency unfolding on land that tests his resolve on the water. And Captain Dave Marciano of Hard Merchandise draws on the support of his wife and daughter far away in Gloucester, Massachusetts, as well as a local family fishing operation to help him get through his slump.

episodes.name: Nine-Foot Monster
episodes.overview: In this episode of Wicked Tuna: Outer Banks, seven crews face the Outer Banks hoping to reel in a fish big enough to keep. But with the luck they have had, prospects are not looking so good. The Fishin’ Frenzy crew lucks out with a big catch and cashes in. With barely a bite, the Doghouse is forced to head in and trust that another day at sea will bring them a big catch. The Hot Tuna crew hopes that their dry spell will end and, with the final reel, they catch one of their largest tuna yet, cashing in over $9,000 for it.

episodes.name: Burn Blubber
episodes.overview: With the North Carolina season coming to a close and Reels of Fortune battling Fishin’ Frenzy for the top spot, all of the crews desperately struggle to land a fish and secure a paycheck. The Reel Action crew fights to catch up but takes a serious blow when they snag a shark; Tyler and Paul lose a “monstah” paycheck; and Dave and the crew of Hard Merchandise attempt to finally end their dry spell, or they’ll have to cut the season short and head back to Gloucester.

episodes.name: On a Fin and a Prayer
episodes.overview: With just five days left before the close of the season, the fleet is feeling the pressure. An accident leaves the Reel Action stuck at the dock, giving Captain Tami and her crew a late start, and tensions onboard reach a boiling point. Meanwhile, the Doghouse and Fishin’ Frenzy have the top spot in sight and are scrambling to keep catching before time runs out. And Captain Griff on the Reels of Fortune finds himself in a dangerous situation while navigating Oregon Inlet — a battle where experience and quick thinking are all that stand between life and death.

episodes.name: Wicked End
episodes.overview: It’s the final two days of the season, and three Southern boats — the Fishin’ Frenzy, the Reels of Fortune and the Doghouse — are all within striking distance of the top spot. As the clock ticks down, the captains are desperate to put meat on deck. The stakes have never been higher: one pulled hook means disaster, but one last catch can mean going home a champion.

episodes.name: Back in the Battle
episodes.overview: It’s bluefin tuna season in the Outer Banks. The fleet is excited to haul in these lucrative giants again — but new obstacles lie ahead.

episodes.name: Wicked Waters
episodes.overview: As the bluefin season takes off, the treacherous waters of the Outer Banks claim another victim, and the Fishin’ Frenzy and Hot Tuna are first on the scene.

episodes.name: A Bluefin for Boo
episodes.overview: The unpredictable waters cause more problems for boats in the Outer Banks. The captains feel the pressure as the season starts to slip away from them.

episodes.name: Underdog Day Afternoon
episodes.overview: With the fishing migration in an unpredictable state, the captains resort to espionage for information but end up with more than they bargained for.

episodes.name: Not How We Operate
episodes.overview: The fifth week of the fishing season becomes a battle for the best fishing spots. The waters turn turbulent as boats go head-to-head to prove their superiority. When old and new rivals clash on the high seas, the pressure is on to land a fish first using strength and intellect.

episodes.name: The Karma Kid
episodes.overview: As the boats are now past the halfway point in the season, the pressure is on to catch enough bluefin tuna to become the No. 1 boat in the fleet.

episodes.name: Old Sailors and Bold Sailors
episodes.overview: Winter kicks into high gear in the Outer Banks and the captains must choose between safety at shore and risking it all at sea to catch bluefin tuna.

episodes.name: Hostile Waters
episodes.overview: The Outer Banks bites back as treacherous waters force captains to choose between chasing the fish at great risk, or waiting until conditions improve.

episodes.name: Striking Distance
episodes.overview: Captain Tyler McLaughlin has stunned the fleet with his surprise comeback, as the other captains struggle to bring in a catch. Time is running out, and the boats must stay out overnight in order to turn their fortunes around.

episodes.name: Luck Be a Tuna Tonight
episodes.overview: Each captain is desperate to bring in one last catch.

episodes.name: Fighting Frenzy
episodes.overview: Last season's champion, Captain Greg Mayer, is determined to land the season's first fish, but he must contend with a new adversary: his former mate.

episodes.name: Full Throttle
episodes.overview: Captain TJ Ott is haunted by a terrifying accident at sea, and the Doghouse desperately tries to land its first fish of the season.

episodes.name: Karma's A Fish
episodes.overview: Captain Greg Mayer sees his lead start to slip away as the competition heats up and one captain brings in the first triple catch of the season.

episodes.name: Dethroned
episodes.overview: Now that reigning champion Fishin' Frenzy's Captain Greg Mayer got knocked off his throne, it's anybody's game in the race for the top spot.

episodes.name: I'll Sleep When I'm Dead
episodes.overview: Most of the fleet fights through exhaustion and fishes round-the-clock in the hopes that one or two great catches could launch them to the top.

episodes.name: Tuna and the Beast
episodes.overview: With two weeks left in the season, every captain in the fleet is feeling the pressure to bring in a bluefin and land a paycheck.

episodes.name: Catch Me If You Can
episodes.overview: As time runs out, the captains fight to bring in their last catches. Greg Mayer has won the last three seasons, can another captain defeat him?

episodes.name: Title Fight
episodes.overview: As time runs out, the captains fight to bring in their last catches. Greg Mayer has won the last three seasons. Can another captain defeat him?

episodes.name: Battle Lines
episodes.overview: It's opening day of the bluefin season, and a reduced quota puts pressure on the captains.

episodes.name: Not in Our Backyard
episodes.overview: The southern fleet has the edge in the Outer Banks for bluefin season.

episodes.name: Reverse the Curse
episodes.overview: A giant school of bluefin tuna breaks the curse for one of the boats, but a few other boats land only bad luck.

episodes.name: Man Overboard
episodes.overview: Local fleets fight the North for their fair share as sustainability strictly limits fishing.

episodes.name: Redemption
episodes.overview: In the most competitive bluefin season yet, some crews are just getting their feet wet.

episodes.name: No Pain, No Gain
episodes.overview: A Southern captain leads the charge against the top-earning Northern boat with the biggest fish of the season, but big fish bring big problems.

episodes.name: Man Down
episodes.overview: When the fleet's best captain is sidelined with an injury, the top spot is available for the taking.

episodes.name: Northern Fury
episodes.overview: The Northern boats’ success continues to frustrate the Southern fishermen.

episodes.name: Old Golly Whopper
episodes.overview: Captain Greg Mayer returns to the helm of the Fishing Frenzy, despite a painful injury.

episodes.name: Blood, Sweat, and Tears
episodes.overview: With a limited number of days left to fish, Tyler chooses between big risk and big reward.

episodes.name: High Speed Chase
episodes.overview: Captain Greg Mayer of the Fishin’ Frenzy is barely holding onto his lead, and the other captains are determined to knock him out of the top spot.

episodes.name: Down to the Wire
episodes.overview: As the clock ticks down, the battle to be the top-earning boat in the Outer Banks heats up.

episodes.name: New Blood
episodes.overview: It’s opening day of bluefin season in the Outer Banks, and a new Southern fleet is ready to take on the Northern captains and defend its home turf.

episodes.name: Bugging Out
episodes.overview: The Southern crew of Reel E’ Bugging fights to prove its place in the competition after a dangerous setback and no bluefin on the leaderboard.

episodes.name: Little Boat, Big Tuna
episodes.overview: While Northern boat Hot Tuna leads the fleet, Southern underdog Rasta Rocket fights to break out of the pack. Can the little boat be big competition?

episodes.name: Hard Knocks
episodes.overview: The fleet learns that, without local knowhow, there’s no chance of conquering this challenging fishery.

episodes.name: Blood Feud
episodes.overview: When a pair of brothers from the South challenge a brother/sister duo from the North for the top spot, the showdown in the Outer Banks becomes a full-blown sibling rivalry.

episodes.name: Reel Outlaws
episodes.overview: With the quota nearly gone, captains push limits to catch what might be final paychecks.

episodes.name: Southern Aggression
episodes.overview: Northern and Southern boats get more bluefin quota, but is it enough to turn the tables?

episodes.name: "Thunder Tuna"
episodes.overview: Extreme weather hits the Outer Banks; the Southern captains, accustomed to the dangerous conditions, believe they have a competitive edge, but the Northern captains are willing to do what it takes to put meat on deck.

episodes.name: The Fast and Furious
episodes.overview: A game-changing fish pits Capt. Zack Shackleford and his young crew on the Rasta Rocket against the fleet's veterans. Northern boat Falcon embraces a new technique to try to stay in the game. The Reel E' Bugging kicks it into overdrive.

episodes.name: No Backing Down
episodes.overview: The Southern fleet fights to keep the lead, but the Northern boats aren't going down easy. When one fish is all it takes to shake things up, the only way to get on top is by taking risks and never backing down.

episodes.name: Miracle Fish
episodes.overview: One fish could make all the difference; a little bit of luck goes a long way.

episodes.name: Storm Troopers
episodes.overview: A storm threatens to cut the season short.

episodes.name: Breaking Point
episodes.overview: The Northern and Southern boats and crews start to break down as the quota closes.

episodes.name: Breaking Point
episodes.overview: The captains are feeling the pressure; even the smallest mistake can torpedo a captain's chance of taking the top spot; Capt. Reed Meredith becomes desperate when mechanical failures threaten to derail his season.

episodes.name: All Out War
episodes.overview: A quota extension creates an all-out frenzy as the captains scramble to land a few more fish before the season ends; Capt. Reed Meredith knows he has what it takes to lead the fleet; northern boats try to keep pace with the southern fleet.

episodes.name: Battle for the Banks
episodes.overview: The Northern and Southern boats fight for the title in the final two days of the season.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview: Several of Gloucester's top fishermen follow bluefin tuna south to the Outer Banks for winter.

episodes.name: Clash of the Titans
episodes.overview: It's opening day in the Outer Banks, and the best captains from both North and South prepare to battle the elements, bluefin and one another.

episodes.name: Stick em
episodes.overview: Will the green stick continue to give the Little Shell an edge, or will the more traditional rod-and-reel rivals prove victorious in the long run?

episodes.name: Family Pride
episodes.overview: With longtime rivals dominating the competition, the brother-sister duo on the Pinwheel struggle to overcome a slow start to their fishing season.

episodes.name: Pay to Play
episodes.overview: Time is money as the captains fish for "blue gold," and when the costs of trying to bring home a bluefin pile up, some captains reevaluate if the benefits of tuna fishing outweigh the drawbacks.

episodes.name: A Fish For Frenzy
episodes.overview: As the top boats solidify their spots in the race, Greg and his mates can't seem to stay in sync, and the former champion boat starts to fall apart.

episodes.name: Never Seen Anything Like It
episodes.overview: The battle for bluefin intensifies as champion boats find the bluefin biting; however, one crew member's loss could alter the rest of the season.

episodes.name: Tricky Dave
episodes.overview: Captain Dave Carraro of the FV-Tuna.com lives up to his "Tricky Dave" reputation when the fleet begins to doubt him after a few sneaky moves.

episodes.name: Hard Times at Sea
episodes.overview: A mate emergency leaves the Hot Tuna struggling to catch a fish. Meanwhile, the Reel E’ Bugging’s crew pushes the limits to get back in the competition.

episodes.name: Make Your Own Luck
episodes.overview: As the quota fills up, the captains must decide if skill or luck is in their favor in order to pull ahead in the competition.

episodes.name: Graveyard Shift
episodes.overview: When winds create treacherous conditions on the Oregon Inlet’s notorious sandbar, captains are faced with the dilemma to triumph or turn around.

episodes.name: Follow The Herd
episodes.overview: The fleet communicates in order to find the fish, but some boats have to follow every lead they hear about, if they want to turn their season around.

episodes.name: Together We Stand
episodes.overview: The tuna titan battle continues while mates try to keep pace. From family ties to lifelong friends, which team has the drive to put meat on the deck?

episodes.name: Reel Tension
episodes.overview: The long, cold winter has just hit New England, and while the bluefin tuna season has come to an end in Gloucester, Mass., it’s just getting started in the Outer Banks of North Carolina. After a disappointing season, several of Gloucester’s top fishermen head south to try to salvage their finances by fishing for the elusive bluefin tuna in unfamiliar Carolina waters before the experienced locals beat them to the catch.

episodes.name: Titan Showdown
episodes.overview: With only two days left, it's a battle of the titans as the captains push to prove they have what it takes to become the next Outer Banks champion.

episodes.name: Danger Lurks
episodes.overview: Another season begins, and the Captains are faced with some old hazards like fire on board and sinking, to new hazards like shifting sands and sunken wrecks, on their main routes out to the fishing grounds.

episodes.name: Beat The Storm
episodes.overview: The Outer Banks fleet battle worsening conditions in the hopes of landing a payday before the forecast rough weather arrives and potentially stops fishing.

episodes.name: Hot Water Big Tuna
episodes.overview: The fleet tries to take advantage of a wave of big fish. With bad weather working against them, the Rasta Rocket is having a hard time fishing, and struggles to keep up with the rest of the fleet.

episodes.name: Doghouse Domination
episodes.overview: It's the toughest season in Outer Banks history. New crews and veteran crews alike battle it out in an effort to catch Blue Gold. The Doghouse proves that they may be the ace crew in the Outer Banks, despite it being their first year as a team, while a mishap on the Reel E' Bugging shows that time on a boat together, isn't everything.

episodes.name: Herd is the Word
episodes.overview: The herds have arrived and for every fisherman in the OBX, this means it's about to be mayhem. A big body of fish brings lower bluefin demand, so it's a race to see who can get a fish before prices dwindle. There is good news for the fleet as a quota extension is announced, which means despite the larger sized fish caught so far this season, the fleet will have more time to make paychecks before the season ends.

episodes.name: Cost to be the Boss
episodes.overview: A risky move by Offshore Outlaw sees the crew taking a short fishing window as a huge storm approaches, and Dog House fights to stay on top.

episodes.name: Fog of War
episodes.overview: While the fleet is docked due to bad weather, one boat takes a chance to get ahead, but facing fog, wind, and high seas, could spell disaster for the attempt.

episodes.name: Hog Tied
episodes.overview: Hog Wild has struggled for most of the season, and they decide that now is the time for a big push to stay in the game.

episodes.name: Triple Trouble
episodes.overview: With the Outer Banks blue fin season half over, Southern hospitality helps one Captain, as the rest of the fleet go all out to hook as many fish as possible.

episodes.name: Risky Business
episodes.overview: The wind wreaks havoc on the fleet, but with over half of the quota already caught, some of them are taking bigger risks than ever to stay ahead.

episodes.name: Pressure Point
episodes.overview: Halfway through the season and another storm front pushing in is starting to put all the fleet under pressure.

episodes.name: Tried and True
episodes.overview: Hog Wild fights to keep the lead, and Captains go back to tried and true methods to increase their catch

episodes.name: Goldrush
episodes.overview: Big fish are everywhere but calm seas and good weather slows catches, and tightly packed boats is a recipe for tension.

episodes.name: Down to the Dollar
episodes.overview: The competition is close and the quota is dwindling, so any major moves will be don to getting top dollar for quality fish.

episodes.name: The Big One
episodes.overview: The quota is still dropping, and the Outer Banks are taking no prisoners no matter whether you or old.

episodes.name: Red Seas
episodes.overview: The fleet wants to prevent Fishin' Frenzy from taking the title but as Greg's hot streak continues this seems to be looking less likely.

episodes.name: Break Point
episodes.overview: With the quota filling up, fishing season in the OBX could end at any moment and the tension on every boat in the fleet is at an all-time high.

episodes.name: One Last Fish
episodes.overview: Less than 24 hrs remain before season shutdown, but with deteriorating weather, the bar is more dangerous than ever and Captains need to decide whether one last fish is worth the risk.

episodes.name: Northern Invasion
episodes.overview: Northern champions face their Southern rivals in the hunt for bluefin tuna during the Outer Banks winter, where only the strong survive.

episodes.name: Danger Zone
episodes.overview: As the Northern fleet looks to bounce back from their slow start, the Reel E. Bugging takes a huge risk in an effort to grab the early season lead.

episodes.name: Perfect Storm
episodes.overview: Northern boat, Pinwheel, risks their lives and their boat on the advice of a Southern Captain in the hope of landing their first fish of the season.

episodes.name: Fair Weather Fish
episodes.overview: In a season of rough weather, there will be a few fishable days in a row and every Captain hopes to capitalize before the storm arrives.

episodes.name: Will vs. Skill
episodes.overview: With the Northern boats docked, the Southern fleet tries to get ahead. Meanwhile, Pinwheel contends with a potentially season-ending malfunction.

episodes.name: Turnaround Times
episodes.overview: The Gloucester champions take advantage of good weather, strategizing to find big bites, and gain ground against the tough Southern competition.

episodes.name: Red Boat Revenge
episodes.overview: Four-time champion Captain Greg Mayer aims to retake the lead, while Captain Robert Earl knows, "A Fish a Day Keeps the Frenzy Away.

episodes.name: No Time for a Slump
episodes.overview: Pinwheel’s Tyler McLaughlin may be in last place now, but the former northern and southern champion spells trouble for the fleet if he gets on a roll.

episodes.name: Brink of Disaster
episodes.overview: It’s survival of the fittest for man and monster fish when danger strikes the Outer Banks and one captain faces his demons.

episodes.name: Tow the Line
episodes.overview: The Southern boats have been dominating the competition all season long, but now the Northern Captains push to make a big move.

episodes.name: Fire on the Little Shell
episodes.overview: Little Shell’s season goes from bad to worse when their gyro breaks loose from its mounts and causes a fire on board.

episodes.name: Sick as a Seadog
episodes.overview: During Pinwheel’s fight back from the bottom, Tyler gets hit with a debilitating illness, putting all the pressure to produce on sister, Marissa.

episodes.name: Blueprint for Bluefin
episodes.overview: When fish become hard to find, strategy becomes the key to catching. Who can outsmart the rest of the fleet to land a bluefin and come out on top?

episodes.name: Beggin for a Bluefin
episodes.overview: As weather windows put a strain on fishing, most of the fleet stays cautious, but Bobby and his mates will do whatever it takes for first place.

episodes.name: Revenge of the Underdogs
episodes.overview: Northern Champ Tyler McLaughlin faces great adversity, while the front-runners look to extend their lead.

episodes.name: Quota Smasher
episodes.overview: Northern champions and Southern rivals battle for bluefin tuna.

episodes.name: The Chase is On
episodes.overview: With Reel E. Bugging in the lead, the rest of the fleet races against the clock to close the gap.

episodes.name: Ultimate Champion
episodes.overview: It’s the last day of fishing and every boat is out trying to make one final paycheck and possibly secure the title - Champion of Champions.
